"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-02-13-Teams-confirmed-for-Paris-2024-women-s-basketball-1r9GAwMjtK0-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  Team China celebrate with a giant Boarding Pass to the Paris 2024 Olympic Games during the FIBA women's Olympic qualifying tournament in Xi'an, China, February 11, 2024. /CFP  All 12 teams of the 2024 Olympic Games' women's basketball competition have been settled through global qualifying tournaments, the International Basketball Federation (FIBA) announced on Tuesday.  Defending champions the United States lead the field, along with Australia, Belgium, China, Canada, Germany, Japan, Serbia, Spain, Nigeria, Puerto Rico and host nation France.  Germany is the only team making a first appearance at an Olympic Games.  Four qualifying tournaments were played in Belgium, China, Hungary and Brazil from February 8 to 11. Ten teams qualified from the tournaments, as the U.S. and France qualified automatically.  The women's basketball competition at Paris 2024 will take place from July 29 to August 11.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"